-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest - Oct 21
-- 
-- Tue Oct 21, 2014 12:05AM EDT
-- None



Oct 21 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* Vitamin Shoppe Inc <VSI.N>, the nutritional supplement retailer under activist shareholder pressure to consider a sale, is speaking to investment banks about hiring a financial adviser, according to people familiar with the matter.[ID:nL2N0SF1W6]  * Allergan Inc <AGN.N> shareholder Paulson & Co is urging the Botox maker to merge with specialty pharmaceutical company Shire Plc <SHP.L> as an alternative to a deal with hostile bidder Valeant Pharmaceuticals <VRX.TO>, according to two people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0SF1CF]  * Australian digital billboard firm APN Outdoor will raise A$329 million ($289 million) in an initial public offer, a person with knowledge of the matter told Reuters, at the bottom of the range its private equity owner had hoped to sell for as appetite for new listings wanes in a weaker stock market. [ID:nL3N0SG1EB]  * Italian drugmaker Sigma-Tau is in advanced talks to sell part of its Italian operations to domestic peer Alfa Wassermann that would create an over-the-counter (OTC) powerhouse, several sources familiar with the situation said. [ID:nL6N0SF3MO]  * Qatar Investment Authority and Hong Kong's Lau family are considering options including a full takeover of department store operator Lifestyle International Holdings Ltd <1212.HK> after the sovereign wealth fund bought a minority stake, Bloomberg reported, citing people with knowledge of the matter. (http://bloom.bg/1sIinYm)  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]